deletedTracks.description: Kevin Locke's spoken vocals introducing a Muskoka song called "Gonna Take Off"
deletedTracks.notes: Recorded when Kevin Locke was passing through London - Sandy captured not just songs but educational backstory about each one. Kevin wasn't happy with his voice due to a cold, but it sounds great. Cultural context: Muskoka is the traditional territory of the Anishnaabeg (Ojibwe, Odawa, Potawatomi) and has also seen the presence of Huron-Wendat and Haudenosaunee peoples, with the name itself coming from an Ojibwe Chief, Musquakie (Mesqua Ukee). Today, several First Nations and M√©tis communities reside in or have ties to Muskoka, including Wahta Mohawks, Moose Deer Point First Nation, Chippewas of Rama, and the Moon River M√©tis, with their lands covered by treaties like the Williams Treaty.
